                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1281-1">BHO, 550.
DTC, VIII, col. 72 (L. Petit).
R. Draquet, ed. et trad., Les cinq recensions de l'Asceticon syriaque d'Abba Isaie
(Louvain, 1968 ; CSCO 289- 90, 293-94, Scr. syri 120-23).
BSO, II, 251- 52 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1281">In hagiography: Isaiah was an ascetic
            from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/289">Scetis</placeName> who founded a
          monastery in <placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/87">Gaza</placeName>. His life was
          written by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/58">Zachariah the Rhetor</persName>. He
          was a friend of Peter the Egyptian.</note>
